---
description: SaaS security essentials — secrets, sanitization, auth, CORS, rate limiting
globs: **/*.ts, **/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
Never store secrets in code — always process.env or vault.
Always sanitize user inputs before DB queries.
Use parameterized queries — never string interpolation in SQL.
Rate limit all public API routes.
Auth checks must happen in middleware, not inside route handlers.
Never log sensitive data: passwords, tokens, PII.
CORS must be explicitly configured, never wildcard in production.
All file uploads must validate type, size, and scan for malware.
No console.log in production code — use a proper logger.
